<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--Style-->
Style Attribute: using the style attribute at the start tag
ex: <tagname style="property:value;">

property and value are CSS things
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Background Color: 
ex: <body style="background-color:powderblue;">Body</body>

It is inside a class or a session start tag
Color value can be text or Hexa value
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Text Color:
ex: <p style="color:red;">Paragraphs</p>

It can be used in any start tag that have texts
Color value can be text or Hexa value
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Border Color
ex: <h1 style="border:_px type color;">Text</h1>

first value is the border's size, second is type (solid, dotted...), and third is color of the line
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Color Value:
1. RGB/RGBA: Intensity of Red, Green, Blue color, A is alpha (transparency)
ex: rgb(r, g, b, a)
r, g, b is range (0-255) and a is (0-1)

2. HEX: Hex value of color
ex: #rrggbb
r,g,b is range (0-f)

3. HSL: Hue, Saturation, Lightness
ex: hsl(h, s, l, a)
h is (0-360), s,l are (0%-100%), a is (0-1)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fonts:
ex: <h1 style="font-family:verdana;">Heading 1</h1>

It can be used in any start tag that have texts
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Text Size:
ex: <h1 style="font-size:300%;">Heading 1</h1>

It can be used in any start tag that have texts
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Text Alignment:
ex: <h1 style="text-align:center;">Heading 1</h1>

It can be used in section or any start tag that have texts
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Formatting Elements
1. Bold: 
ex: <b>Bold</b>
2. Strong:
ex: <strong>Important</strong>
3. Italic:
ex: <i>Italic</i>
4. Emphasis:
ex: <em>Emphasis</em>
5. Small text:
ex: <small>Small text</small>
6. Mark/Highlighted:
ex: <mark>Marked</mark>
7. Strike a line:
ex: <del>Line</del>
8. Insert: Inserted is used after one is deleted (Striked the line)
ex: <ins>sth</ins> 
comes with underline
9. Subscript: Like the 2 in H2O
ex: H<sub>2</sub>O
10. Superscript: Like the exponent
ex: x<sup>4</sup>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Quotation and Citation Elements
1. From other sources (will be indented)
ex: <blockquote cite="source">quote</blockquote>
2. Short quotation
ex: <q>Short quote</q>
3. Abbreviations
ex: <abbr title="Full Name">FN</abbr>
4. Address for contact information (Italic)
ex: <address>Info1 <br>Info2 </address>
5. Cite for Work Title (Italic)
ex: <cite>Title</cite>
6. Bi-Directional Override
ex: <bdo dir="direction">message</bdo>

direction can be rtl or ltr (right to left or left to right)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
